rockets gonna relive groots death all over again, and is gonna have to mourn his whole family, not just groot.

body:
COPYCAT PT. 1

Fandom: Marvel (Spider-Man)

Song prompt: ‘Copycat’ - Billie Eilish

Sentence prompts: (1. “I don’t understand why you did this”) & (2. “What is going on?!”) & (22. “You’re mine”)

Pairing: Reader x Peter Parker, also a bit of Reader x Refrigerator ;)

Warnings: None

Words: Idk, probably over 1000

Requested: Nope

-

Don’t be cautious, don’t be kind

You committed, I’m your crime

-

I walked down the empty hallway, the linoleum floor squeaking under my sneakers. My footsteps echoed in the wide space as I made my way to the front of the school. I glanced up at a classroom on my right. Inside was the Math Club. Peter Parker, one of the guys in my year, looked up at me. We made eye contact and he smiled at me. I blushed, gave a slight smile back and picked up my pace. It wasn’t anything out of the ordinary, I regularly lost my cool over Parker. It’s almost as if whenever I tried to avoid him so I wouldn’t make a fool out of myself, he would pop up out of nowhere. I sighed as I made my way into the cool evening air.

-

Push my button anytime

You got your finger on the trigger, but your trigger finger’s mine

-

I had stayed back to work on my latest project for Fashion Design. I was designing my own ball gown in different shades of pretty greens, as my theme was nature. I was planning on adding small flowers into the gossamer layers. Overall my vision was similar to a field of flowers. So I stayed behind to complete my draft designs to get more done in one day. I made my way to the bus stop and put my earphones in and pressed play on my phone. My favourite song at the moment came on and I leaned my head back slightly, revelling in the memory of Peter’s face. The way his pencil sat placed in between his pink lips, the way one curl of hair fell over his face as he looked down at his paper. I turned my head my head to see the bus approaching. I stood up and entered the opening doors.

-

Silver dollar, golden flame

Dirty water, poison rain

-

The bus ride was uneventful as usual. I got off in front of my house and walked to the front door. I unlocked it, swung open the door and stepped inside. “Anyone home?” I called. No answer. I walked to my favourite part of the house, the kitchen. As I opened the fridge, the bright white light and misty coolness invited me to reach my hand in. And reach in I did, grabbing a medium container of leftovers and placing it in the microwave and setting the time. I leaned against the counter and thought about Peter. How he laughed when Ned told him a joke at lunch and his quietly spoken, intelligent observations in class.

-

Perfect murder, take your aim

I don’t belong to anyone, but everybody knows my name

-

I ate my food from the container, not wanting to wash more dishes than I had to. I finished up and washed the few plates in the sink and the new additions. I walked up the stairs to my room and flopped onto the bed. I huffed and sat up, grabbing my laptop to do some research for History. When I thought I had done enough, I grabbed my phone and saw a new message from MJ. ‘Y/N, do you have the notes from class today? I just checked my bag and I can’t find mine. I must have left them on the bus or something. Can I borrow yours?’ I giggled and replied to her text with ‘Yeah sure no sweat, just remind me tomorrow’. My phone lit up a few moments later, showing me her new message ‘Thank you thank you thank you, you are the bestest friend in the world!’ ‘Yeah, yeah you’re welcome’, I smiled as I sent the message. I put my phone to charge and changed into my pjs. Turning off the light, I climbed into bed and drifted off, dreaming sweet dreams of the object of my affections, Peter Parker.

-

Thank you so much for reading, please leave feedback and request away! Part 2 will be coming out as well ✌🏽

This is also part of @toms-order‘s Not A Challenge Challenge, so thanks so much @toms-order for inspiring me to write!

If you’d like to you can follow my photography blog, @sophie-rebecca17
